 is possible that, due to any number of reasons, including, but not limited to, an unfavorable fluctuation in the value of ETH (or other cryptographic and fiat currencies), decrease in CIPHER utility due to negative adoption of the CIPHER Platform, the failure of commercial relationships, or intellectual property ownership challenges, the CIPHER Platform may no longer be viable to operate and the Company may dissolve.</span></p></li></ol><br><ol style="margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px;" start="16"><li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; margin-left: -18pt;" aria-level="1"><p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.365;margin-right: -0.5pt;text-align: justify;margin-top:1.25pt;margin-bottom:8pt;" role="presentation"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Risks arising from lack of governance rights</span><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">: because CIPHER&nbsp; confer no governance rights of any kind&nbsp; with&nbsp; respect&nbsp; to&nbsp; the&nbsp; CIPHER &nbsp; Platform&nbsp; or&nbsp; Company;&nbsp; all&nbsp; decisions&nbsp; involving&nbsp; Company (including to sell or liquidate Company) will be made by Company acting in its sole and absolute discretion, and all decisions involving the CIPHER&nbsp; Platform including, but not limited to, decisions to discontinue the CIPHER&nbsp; Platform, to create and issue more CIPHER , will be made by the Company. These decisions could adversely affect the CIPHER Platform and/or CIPHER you hold.</span></p></li></ol><br><ol style="margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-